Gold Drops for Fifth Day, Heading for Longest Losing Streak Since January

-- B y   G l e n y s   S i m
-- 
2011-10-20T23:10:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/gold-drops-for-fifth-day-heading-for-longest-losing-streak-since-january.html
Gold for immediate delivery fell for
a fifth day, the longest period of decline since January,
dropping as much as 0.6 percent to $1,611.82 an ounce. The metal
traded at $1,613.88 at 7:08 a.m. Singapore time, down 4 percent
this week and poised for its first weekly decrease in three
weeks.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Glenys Sim at 
 gsim4@bloomberg.net  